﻿@{
    string Title = "Privacy Policy";
    ViewData["Title"] = Title;
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    This privacy policy explains how we collect, use and protect your personal information when you use our dad jojes app
</p>

<h2>What information do we collect?</h2>

<p>
    We collect the following information from you when you use our app:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Your device information, such as your device model, operating system, browser type, and IP address.</li>
    <li>
        Your usage information, such as the jokes you view, like, share, or save in our app.
    </li>
    <li>
        Your feedback and ratings on our app and the jokes.
    </li>
    <li>
        Your contact information, such as your email address, if you choose to sign up for our newsletter or contact us for support.
    </li>
</ul>

<p>
    We do not collect any sensitive information from you, such as your name, address, phone number, credit card details, or social security number.
</p>

<h2>How do we use your information?</h2>

<p>
    We use your information for the following purposes:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        To provide and improve our app and its features, such as displaying jokes that match your preferences, showing you relevant ads, and fixing bugs and errors.
    </li>
    <li>
        To communicate with you, such as sending you newsletters, updates, promotions, and notifications about our app and the jokes.
    </li>
    <li>
        To monitor and analyze our app performance, such as measuring user engagement, traffic, and trends.
    </li>
    <li>
        To protect our app and its users, such as detecting and preventing fraud, spam, abuse, and unauthorized access.
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>How do we protect your information?</h2>

<p>
    We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, modification, or destruction. We use secure servers, encryption, firewalls, and other security technologies to store and transfer your information. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.
</p>

<h2>How do we share your information?</h2>

<p>
    We do not sell, rent, or trade your information to any third parties for their own purposes. We may share your information with the following parties for the purposes described above:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        Our service providers, such as cloud hosting providers, database providers, analytics providers, advertising providers, and email providers. They only have access to the information they need to perform their services for us and are contractually obligated to protect your information and use it only in accordance with our instructions.
    </li>
    <li>
        Our affiliates and partners, such as other apps or websites that offer dad jokes or related content. They may use your information to show you personalized content and ads on their platforms. You can opt out of this by changing your settings in our app or their platforms.
    </li>
    <li>
        Law enforcement authorities or other parties when required by law or when necessary to protect our rights or interests. We may disclose your information if we believe in good faith that it is necessary to comply with a legal obligation, respond to a lawful request, enforce our terms of service, prevent or address fraud or security issues, or protect the rights or property of ourselves or others.
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>
    How do we use cookies and other tracking technologies?
</h2>

<p>
    We use cookies and other tracking technologies to collect and store your information when you use our app. Cookies are small files that are stored on your device by your browser. They allow us to recognize your device and remember your preferences and settings. Other tracking technologies include web beacons, pixels, tags, and scripts that are embedded in our app or emails. They help us measure the effectiveness of our app and communications.
</p>

<p>
    We use cookies and other tracking technologies for the following purposes:

</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        To provide and improve our app functionality and performance

    </li>
    <li>
        To personalize your experience and content on our app

    </li>
    <li>
        To deliver relevant ads on our app and other platforms

    </li>
    <li>
        To analyze our app usage and traffic

    </li>
    <li>
        To monitor and prevent fraud and security issues

    </li>
</ul>

<h2>
    What are your choices and rights regarding your information?
</h2>

<p>
    You have the following choices and rights regarding your information:

</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        You can access, update, correct, or delete your information by contacting us at @ViewData["EmailAddress"]. We may ask you to verify your identity before fulfilling your request.

    </li>
    <li>
        You can opt out of receiving newsletters, updates, promotions, and notifications from us by clicking on the unsubscribe link in our emails or changing your settings in our app.

    </li>
    <li>
        You can withdraw your consent to our use of your information at any time by contacting us at @ViewData["EmailAddress"]. However, this will not affect the lawfulness of any processing that occurred before your withdrawal.

    </li>
    <li>
        You can lodge a complaint with a data protection authority if you believe that we have violated your rights or the applicable data protection laws.

    </li>
</ul>

<h2>How do we handle children's information?</h2>

<p>
    Our app is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect or solicit any information from anyone under the age of 13. If we become aware that we have collected information from a child under the age of 13, we will delete it as soon as possible. If you are a parent or guardian and you believe that your child has provided us with information without your consent, please contact us at [our email address] and we will take appropriate steps to remove it.


</p>

<h2>
    How do we update our privacy policy?
</h2>

<p>
    We may update our privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technologies, or legal requirements. We will notify you of any material changes by posting a notice on our app or sending you an email. The date at the top of this privacy policy indicates when it was last updated. Your continued use of our app after we make changes is deemed to be acceptance of those changes. Please review this privacy policy periodically to stay informed about how we collect, use, and protect your information.
</p>

<h2>
    How do you contact us?
</h2>

<p>
    If you have any questions, comments, or concerns about this privacy policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at @ViewData["EmailAddress"]. We will respond to your inquiry as soon as possible.
</p>